#: ../../source/concepts.md:1
msgid "Concepts"
msgstr "核心概念"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:3
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"This page explains the **mental model** behind IR-SIM — how the pieces fit "
"together and why the API looks the way it does. Read it once; the {doc}`User"
" Guide <usage/index>` then shows how to do specific tasks, and the "
"{doc}`Configuration <yaml_config/index>` reference documents every key."
msgstr ""
"本页讲解 IR-SIM 背后的**思维模型**——各部分如何协作，以及 API 为何如此设计。建议先通读一遍；之后 {doc}`用户指南 "
"<usage/index>` 会演示如何完成具体任务，而 {doc}`配置 <yaml_config/index>` 参考则记录了每一个配置键。"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:5
msgid "The big picture"
msgstr "总体框架"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:7
msgid ""
"A scene in IR-SIM is a **World** plus a set of **Objects** (robots and "
"obstacles). Objects can carry **sensors** and be driven by **behaviors**. "
"You describe the whole scene declaratively in YAML, create it with "
"`irsim.make()`, and advance it one time step at a time."
msgstr ""
"IR-SIM "
"中的一个场景由一个**世界**（World）和一组**对象**（机器人与障碍物）组成。对象可以携带**传感器**，并由**行为**驱动。你以声明式的方式在"
" YAML 中描述整个场景，用 `irsim.make()` 创建它，然后逐个时间步推进。"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:26
msgid "The environment"
msgstr "环境"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:28
msgid ""
"The **environment** (`EnvBase`) is the object you interact with. It owns the"
" world and every object, and it exposes the simulation **lifecycle**:"
msgstr "**环境**（`EnvBase`）是你直接交互的对象。它拥有世界和每一个对象，并暴露仿真的**生命周期**："

#: ../../source/concepts.md:30
msgid ""
"**`make()`** — parse the YAML scenario and build the world and objects."
msgstr "**`make()`** —— 解析 YAML 场景并构建世界与对象。"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:31
msgid ""
"**`step()`** — advance every object by one time step: apply each object's "
"behavior (or an external command), integrate its kinematics, then refresh "
"sensors and collision state."
msgstr "**`step()`** —— 将每个对象推进一个时间步：应用对象的行为（或外部指令），积分其运动学，然后刷新传感器与碰撞状态。"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:32
msgid "**`render()`** — draw the current state with Matplotlib."
msgstr "**`render()`** —— 用 Matplotlib 绘制当前状态。"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:33
msgid ""
"**`done()`** — report whether a terminal condition has been reached (e.g. "
"all robots arrived, or a collision)."
msgstr "**`done()`** —— 报告是否达到终止条件（例如所有机器人到达目标，或发生碰撞）。"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:34
msgid ""
"**`reset()` / `reload()`** — restore objects to their initial states, or "
"rebuild the scene from YAML."
msgstr "**`reset()` / `reload()`** —— 将对象恢复到初始状态，或从 YAML 重新构建场景。"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:35
msgid ""
"**`end()`** — close the window and release resources (and write the "
"animation if `save_ani=True`)."
msgstr "**`end()`** —— 关闭窗口并释放资源（若 `save_ani=True` 则写出动画）。"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:37
msgid "This `step → render → done` loop is the heart of every IR-SIM program."
msgstr "这个 `step → render → done` 循环是每个 IR-SIM 程序的核心。"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:39
msgid "The world"
msgstr "世界"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:41
msgid ""
"The **World** holds the global state that objects live in: the size "
"(`width`, `height`), the clock (`step_time` for physics, `sample_time` for "
"rendering), the coordinate frame (`offset`), an optional **obstacle map** "
"(an occupancy grid), and the **collision detector**. Collision checking uses"
" [Shapely](https://shapely.readthedocs.io/) geometry with a spatial index, "
"so it scales to many objects."
msgstr ""
"**世界**（World）保存着对象所处的全局状态：尺寸（`width`、`height`）、时钟（用于物理的 `step_time` 与用于渲染的 "
"`sample_time`）、坐标系（`offset`）、可选的**障碍物地图**（占据栅格），以及**碰撞检测器**。碰撞检测使用 "
"[Shapely](https://shapely.readthedocs.io/) 几何与空间索引，因此可扩展到大量对象。"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:43
msgid "Objects: robots and obstacles"
msgstr "对象：机器人与障碍物"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:45
msgid ""
"Everything placed in the scene is an **object**. Robots and obstacles share "
"the same machinery — the difference is mostly their *role* and whether they "
"are actively controlled. Each object has:"
msgstr "场景中放置的一切都是**对象**。机器人和障碍物共享同一套机制——区别主要在于它们的*角色*以及是否被主动控制。每个对象都有："

#: ../../source/concepts.md:47
msgid ""
"**State** — its pose, represented as a column vector `[x, y, theta]` (some "
"kinematics add dimensions). This is what `step()` integrates and what "
"sensors and collisions are computed from."
msgstr ""
"**状态** —— 它的位姿，表示为列向量 `[x, y, theta]`（某些运动学会增加维度）。这正是 `step()` "
"所积分的量，也是传感器与碰撞计算的依据。"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:48
msgid ""
"**Kinematics** — how a velocity command turns into motion: `diff` "
"(differential drive), `omni` (omnidirectional), `omni_angular`, or `acker` "
"(Ackermann / car-like). An object with no kinematics is *static*."
msgstr ""
"**运动学** —— 速度指令如何转化为运动：`diff`（差速驱动）、`omni`（全向）、`omni_angular` 或 `acker`（阿克曼 "
"/ 类汽车）。没有运动学的对象即为*静态*对象。"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:49
msgid ""
"**Shape** — `circle`, `rectangle`, `polygon`, or `linestring`, used for both"
" collision and drawing."
msgstr "**形状** —— `circle`、`rectangle`、`polygon` 或 `linestring`，同时用于碰撞与绘制。"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:50
msgid ""
"**Goal** — an optional target pose; arrival is detected within a distance "
"threshold."
msgstr "**目标** —— 可选的目标位姿；在一定距离阈值内即判定为到达。"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:52
msgid "Behaviors: deciding what to do"
msgstr "行为：决定要做什么"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:54
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"A **behavior** maps an object's state (and, for reactive ones, its "
"neighbours) to a velocity command on every step. The built-ins are `dash` "
"(head straight to the goal), `rvo` (reciprocal velocity obstacles), and "
"`sfm` (social force model), plus the group behavior `orca` (optimal "
"reciprocal collision avoidance). You don't have to use a behavior at all — "
"you can drive an object yourself by passing a command to `env.step(action)`,"
" or {doc}`register your own behavior <usage/configure_behavior>`."
msgstr ""
"**行为**在每一步将对象的状态（对于反应式行为，还包括其邻居）映射为速度指令。内置行为有 `dash`（直奔目标）、`rvo`（互惠速度障碍）和 "
"`sfm`（社会力模型），以及群体行为 `orca`（最优互惠避碰）。你也完全可以不使用行为——通过向 `env.step(action)` "
"传入指令来自行驱动对象，或 {doc}`注册自定义行为 <usage/configure_behavior>`。"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:56
msgid "Sensors: perceiving the world"
msgstr "传感器：感知世界"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:58
msgid ""
"**Sensors** are attached to objects and produce measurements from the world "
"each step: a 2D LiDAR, a 2D FMCW LiDAR (range *and* per-beam radial "
"velocity), and a field-of-view detector. Sensors are refreshed **after** "
"objects move, so a reading always reflects the latest world state."
msgstr ""
"**传感器**附着在对象上，每一步从世界产生测量：2D 激光雷达、2D FMCW "
"激光雷达（距离*以及*每束的径向速度）和视场检测器。传感器在对象移动**之后**刷新，因此读数始终反映最新的世界状态。"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:60
msgid "From YAML to a running scene"
msgstr "从 YAML 到运行的场景"

#: ../../source/concepts.md:62
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"IR-SIM is **declarative**. The `world`, `robot`, and `obstacle` blocks in "
"your YAML are turned into `World` and object instances by an internal "
"factory — which is why you rarely write imperative setup code. You "
"*describe* the scene and IR-SIM builds it, so the same scenario file can be "
"shared, version-controlled, and reused across experiments. The "
"{doc}`Configuration <yaml_config/configuration>` reference documents every "
"available key."
msgstr ""
"IR-SIM 是**声明式**的。YAML 中的 `world`、`robot` 与 `obstacle` 块由内部工厂转化为 `World` "
"与对象实例——因此你很少需要编写命令式的初始化代码。你*描述*场景，IR-SIM "
"负责构建，于是同一个场景文件可以被共享、纳入版本控制，并在不同实验间复用。{doc}`配置 <yaml_config/configuration>` "
"参考记录了每一个可用的配置键。"

